  "prompt": "Has a movie ever been shot in space?",
  "response": "While no full-length feature film has been entirely shot in space, there have been some space-related filming activities:\n\n1. In 2021, a Russian film crew, including actress Yulia Peresild and director Klim Shipenko, traveled to the International Space Station (ISS) and shot parts of a movie called \"The Challenge\" (\u0412\u044b\u0437\u043e\u0432), which was the first narrative film partially filmed in actual space.\n\n2. In 2022, Tom Cruise announced plans to work with NASA and SpaceX to shoot a movie on the ISS, though this project is still in development.\n\nMost space-related movies are filmed on Earth using sets, special effects, and zero-gravity simulation techniques. While portions of documentaries and scientific footage have been shot in space, a complete narrative film shot entirely in space has not yet occurred.",
